description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting position for a kind and compassionate Nursery Nurse to join our nursery team in Hunnitots to provide care for children aged 4 months to 5 yrs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hunnitots Day Nursery has approximately 75 children booked in each day. Parents have a choice of in excess of 10 different sessions within the hours of 7am to 6.00pm. The choice provided aims to accommodate the variety of staff working patterns in the Ipswich Hospital NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hunnitots has a combination of 26 full and part time staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires some key skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A patient, caring, calm, yet assertive and responsible nature,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NNEB/Btech or NVQ level 3 or equivalent in Food hygiene &amp;Child protection&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with children aged 4 months to 5 years of age&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team player&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a motivated and creative person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Knowledge &amp; understanding of early learning (EYFS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE READ THE ATTACHED JOB DESCRIPTION AND PERSON SPECIFICATION BEFORE APPLYING.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you have the right skills for this exciting position and for more information Please contact Mrs J Naylor on 01473 704514 or Annemarie.davies@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
